00:46:56,093 --> 00:46:57,822
You have to
pass the 12 twice

765
00:46:58,596 --> 00:47:00,154
This stem is very tight,
isn't it?

766
00:47:00,231 --> 00:47:02,597
Oh, yes You know, I was
afraid to turn it at all

767
00:47:02,666 --> 00:47:06,067
You see, I figured
anything that tight
wasn't supposed to move

768
00:47:06,137 --> 00:47:07,832
Thank you very much
for trying to do that

769
00:47:07,905 --> 00:47:10,203
Oh, that's all right
I do it all day long

770
00:47:10,407 --> 00:47:13,035
Showed Mr Shaeffer
how to do it
for 20 minutes

771
00:47:13,110 --> 00:47:15,442
It took me another 20 minutes
to explain it to him,

772
00:47:15,513 --> 00:47:17,310
with the manager
leaning on the door

773
00:47:17,381 --> 00:47:20,316
Finally, I told him
I'd be glad to turn it
a day ahead for him then

774
00:47:20,384 --> 00:47:22,318
But he said,
"No, if you're gonna have
a calendar watch,

775
00:47:22,386 --> 00:47:23,978
you might as well
have the right day"

776
00:47:25,055 --> 00:47:26,386
There you go, Lieutenant
All set

777
00:47:26,457 --> 00:47:27,424
Oh, thank you

778
00:47:27,491 --> 00:47:30,085
And thank you very much
for your cooperation

779
00:47:30,161 --> 00:47:31,185
Not at all

780
00:47:31,395 --> 00:47:34,262
Oh, incidentally,
I like your hair

781
00:47:34,565 --> 00:47:35,554
Darryl?

782
00:47:37,368 --> 00:47:38,699
Uh, yes

783
00:47:39,537 --> 00:47:40,526
Thought so

784
00:47:40,938 --> 00:47:41,927
Yeah

