for you, Mrs Brandt

814
00:49:33,450 --> 00:49:36,613
No, go ahead
It's all right
I can take it

815
00:49:37,221 --> 00:49:38,381
God help me

816
00:49:38,455 --> 00:49:40,889
Well, nothing
that bad

817
00:49:40,991 --> 00:49:43,653
I mean, I'm just gonna
ask a few questions

818
00:49:43,727 --> 00:49:45,888
Oh, God!
It was all so awful

819
00:49:47,197 --> 00:49:49,256
Maybe I should come back
another time

820
00:49:49,333 --> 00:49:52,734
No I can't give in
like this I can't

821
00:49:54,204 --> 00:49:55,694
I'm not what I seem
to be, Lieutenant

822
00:49:55,773 --> 00:49:57,206
I'm not made of lace

823
00:49:57,274 --> 00:49:58,468
Never was

824
00:49:58,909 --> 00:50:00,035
When I was a girl,

825
00:50:00,110 --> 00:50:02,078
people used to say
I got my own way
about everything

826
00:50:02,146 --> 00:50:04,376
because I was
lovelylooking

827
00:50:05,049 --> 00:50:07,483
Perhaps so, but that
wasn't the only reason

828
00:50:07,551 --> 00:50:08,984
I had strength then

829
00:50:09,787 --> 00:50:11,049
I have it still

830
00:50:12,189 --> 00:50:13,622
I must be strong now

831
00:50:14,658 --> 00:50:17,286
'Cause that's the way
he would have wanted it

832
00:50:22,266 --> 00:50:24,791
All right, Lieutenant
Examine me

833
00:50:26,737 --> 00:50:31,538
No, no, look, Mrs Brandt,
it's a very tragic thing

834
00:50:32,242 --> 00:50:36,576
If you ever feel faint while
I'm asking you questions,

835
00:50:36,680 --> 00:50:38,011
you'll let me know

836
00:50:38,148 --> 00:50:40,981
I mean, the last thing
I wanna do is upset you

837
00:50:41,051 --> 00:50:43,952
(SOBBING DRAMATICALLY)
Oh! Oh!
I'm sorry, I'm sorry

838
00:50:44,555 --> 00:50:45,988
(CLOTH RIPPING)

839
00:50:54,832 --> 00:50:56,197
Well, thank you,
Mrs Brandt

840
00:50:56,300 --> 00:50:58,234
That's all the questions
for today

841
00:50:58,435 --> 00:50:59,527
Thank you

