00:51:00,671 --> 00:51:01,899
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

843
00:51:03,073 --> 00:51:04,404
Yes?

844
00:51:06,410 --> 00:51:07,536
Are you all right?

845
00:51:08,178 --> 00:51:09,873
Sure Are you?

846
00:51:10,347 --> 00:51:11,541
Fine, considering

847
00:51:12,282 --> 00:51:13,749
You better put
a robe on or something

848
00:51:13,817 --> 00:51:15,717
Lieutenant Columbo is here
to ask some questions

849
00:51:16,320 --> 00:51:20,051
Hell of a thing
Makes you grow up
kind of fast

850
00:51:23,660 --> 00:51:27,255
Yes Yes
Death does do that

851
00:51:29,133 --> 00:51:30,498
My father's didn't

852
00:51:31,068 --> 00:51:33,195
I don't remember
very much
about his death

853
00:51:33,771 --> 00:51:35,898
No reason you should
You were very small

854
00:51:36,240 --> 00:51:38,299
I wonder why Mother
never remarried

855
00:51:39,676 --> 00:51:42,236
You know,
this is the first time
I ever wondered that?

856
00:51:42,312 --> 00:51:44,177
She didn't fall
in love, I expect

857
00:51:45,783 --> 00:51:47,808
Love? Mother?

858
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:52,652
You protect her
when you're talking to me,

859
00:51:53,223 --> 00:51:55,953
the same way you protect me
when you're talking to her

860
00:51:56,360 --> 00:51:57,850
You protect everybody

861
00:51:58,061 --> 00:51:59,050
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

862
00:52:00,230 --> 00:52:02,630
Excuse me, I don't mean
to intrude or anything

863
00:52:03,167 --> 00:52:05,192
You're not intruding,
Lieutenant Come in

864
00:52:05,469 --> 00:52:07,027
I just dropped by
on the way to my room

865
00:52:07,104 --> 00:52:08,469
to see if Janie
was all right

866
00:52:09,039 --> 00:52:10,165
Excuse me

867
00:52:17,347 --> 00:52:21,545
I wonder if I could just
ask you a couple of things,
Miss Janie?

868
00:52:22,886 --> 00:52:23,944
Janie will do

869
00:52:25,622 --> 00:52:26,611
Sure, why not?

870
00:52:27,024 --> 00:52:30,482
Nothing personal
or anything I mean,
it's just routine, you know

871
00:52:31,395 --> 00:52:33,192
I'm supposed
to ask questions

872
00:52:33,297 --> 00:52:37,495
You want to know
where I was at the time
of the murder, right?

873
00:52:38,635 --> 00:52:39,693
Yes

874
00:52:42,506 --> 00:52:44,030
I was with a lover

875
00:52:44,808 --> 00:52:48,175
and I won't give his name
unless it becomes
absolutely necessary

876
00:52:50,080 --> 00:52:51,104
Right

877
00:52:52,082 --> 00:52:53,106
Well, then,

878
00:52:53,450 --> 00:52:54,439
thank you

879
00:53:08,232 --> 00:53:09,529
(WATER RUNNING LOUDLY)

880
00:53:12,169 --> 00:53:13,158
Excuse me

881
00:53:16,006 --> 00:53:17,735
Gee, I'm sorry

882
00:53:17,808 --> 00:53:20,208
I knocked twice
I really did

883
00:53:21,445 --> 00:53:23,174
I was in the kitchen
the whole time

884
00:53:23,247 --> 00:53:24,407
Ask anybody

885
00:53:35,826 --> 00:53:38,795
Oh, boy! Thanks

886
00:53:41,365 --> 00:53:43,265
Well, you've got some family,
Miss Lytton

887
00:53:43,333 --> 00:53:45,893
Everybody thinks
I'm getting ready
to arrest them

888
00:53:46,169 --> 00:53:47,363
Everybody but me

889
00:53:47,804 --> 00:53:49,738
Yes, it's a relief,
talking to you

890
00:53:49,806 --> 00:53:51,637
I was beginning
to feel like a policeman

891
00:53:51,975 --> 00:53:54,876
You are a policeman,
and a good one

892
00:53:55,345 --> 00:53:58,109
You say a thing
when you're ready to say it
and not before

893
00:53:59,550 --> 00:54:00,881
You know how to keep a secret

894
00:54:01,919 --> 00:54:03,682
What kind of secret?

895
00:54:04,521 --> 00:54:06,250
I just know that you have one

896
00:54:06,523 --> 00:54:07,512
I know the look

897
00:54:08,926 --> 00:54:11,793
My brotherinlaw had
that look the day he died

898
00:54:11,862 --> 00:54:15,491
Does Janie know
that you and her father
were once engaged?

899
00:54:15,866 --> 00:54:18,027
Of course
I have no secrets from Janie

900
00:54:18,936 --> 00:54:20,028
None?

901
00:54:20,270 --> 00:54:21,794
Only one

902
00:54:23,206 --> 00:54:26,767
I gather that you've been
reading old society columns
and birth certificates

903
00:54:28,545 --> 00:54:31,912
I became curious
when you told me
about Peter Brandt

904
00:54:33,050 --> 00:54:36,315
Lieutenant, that is
a part of my life that
I don't discuss with anyone,

905
00:54:36,553 --> 00:54:39,522
and I don't feel
that I know you well enough
to discuss it with you now

906
00:54:40,023 --> 00:54:42,321
None of my business
I'm sorry

907
00:54:44,194 --> 00:54:47,595
Oh, by the way, I do have
one little problem,
Miss Lytton

908
00:54:49,499 --> 00:54:50,989
It's about the alibis

909
00:54:51,268 --> 00:54:53,634
Aren't you satisfied
that we were all
telling the truth

910
00:54:53,704 --> 00:54:55,797
about where we were
at the time of the murders?

911
00:54:56,506 --> 00:54:58,406
The problem is,

912
00:54:59,910 --> 00:55:02,572
the murders didn't
take place at 9:00

