00:55:04,848 --> 00:55:07,749
I thought you said
that Mr Shaeffer
made a phone call

914
00:55:07,818 --> 00:55:10,446
into an answering machine
on a tape,

915
00:55:10,520 --> 00:55:11,953
and that he
mentioned the time

916
00:55:12,022 --> 00:55:13,011
He did

917
00:55:13,390 --> 00:55:14,721
He was lying

918
00:55:15,192 --> 00:55:18,423
I understand the note
that Mr Shaeffer had now

919
00:55:18,495 --> 00:55:20,963
The one that said,
"Turn ahead twice
at midnight"

920
00:55:21,832 --> 00:55:23,857
I have no idea
what you're talking about

921
00:55:23,934 --> 00:55:26,425
Mr Shaeffer had
a calendar watch
like mine

922
00:55:27,437 --> 00:55:30,497
It has to be set
to May 1st by hand

923
00:55:30,907 --> 00:55:33,000
In order to do that,
you have to

924
00:55:33,543 --> 00:55:36,979
turn it past the 12 twice
after midnight

925
00:55:38,882 --> 00:55:43,080
Mr Shaeffer's watch
had been set to May 1st

926
00:55:44,321 --> 00:55:48,883
That means he was probably
still alive at midnight

927
00:55:50,894 --> 00:55:52,259
How can you be sure of that?

928
00:55:52,729 --> 00:55:55,163
The salesman
where he bought the watch

929
00:55:55,232 --> 00:55:59,532
said that he explained
how it worked to Mr Shaeffer
for 20 minutes

930
00:55:59,603 --> 00:56:01,594
because Mr Shaeffer said,

931
00:56:01,672 --> 00:56:05,073
"lf you're gonna have
a calendar watch, you might
as well have the right day"

932
00:56:05,809 --> 00:56:07,970
And in order to have
the right day,

933
00:56:08,445 --> 00:56:14,873
he would have to
turn the watch twice
right after midnight,

934
00:56:15,452 --> 00:56:17,113
just as the note said

935
00:56:18,522 --> 00:56:20,683
How brilliant
you are, Lieutenant

936
00:56:22,659 --> 00:56:25,526
Tell me,
why would he lie?

937
00:56:27,130 --> 00:56:30,224
Why would he want
everyone to believe that
it was earlier than it was?

938
00:56:30,734 --> 00:56:32,793
That's what I can't
figure out, ma'am

939
00:56:34,905 --> 00:56:35,894
Unless

940
00:56:36,073 --> 00:56:37,734
Unless somebody
told him to

941
00:56:40,310 --> 00:56:43,473
Yes, but why would somebody
tell him to, ma'am?

942
00:56:45,515 --> 00:56:48,678
Lieutenant, I do wish
you would stop trying
to trip me up

943
00:56:48,752 --> 00:56:51,346
You know the answer to that
You just said it yourself

944
00:56:52,355 --> 00:56:54,585
At 9:00 everyone had an alibi

945
00:56:55,292 --> 00:56:59,126
But even if you're right
and somebody told him
to do it, why did he listen?

946
00:57:00,664 --> 00:57:04,464
I mean, why provide
somebody with an alibi,
time and all,

947
00:57:04,534 --> 00:57:05,967
by pretending to die?

948
00:57:07,137 --> 00:57:08,900
Obviously, he didn't think
it was an alibi,

949
00:57:08,972 --> 00:57:10,769
because he didn't think
he was going to die

950
00:57:11,775 --> 00:57:13,606
Since Edward
didn't shoot him,

951
00:57:15,178 --> 00:57:17,442
someone else must have
made an arrangement with him

952
00:57:18,348 --> 00:57:21,374
Someone who wanted him dead
and who wanted an alibi

953
00:57:21,885 --> 00:57:23,614
Suppose they planned
the robbery together,

954
00:57:23,687 --> 00:57:25,678
Mr Shaeffer and the man
who shot him,

955
00:57:26,556 --> 00:57:28,751
and all Shaeffer
was planning to do

956
00:57:28,925 --> 00:57:32,884
was to leave the country
with some antique gold jewelry
worth quite a lot of money

957
00:57:34,164 --> 00:57:36,860
But, then, let's say
that the cohort shot him,

958
00:57:36,933 --> 00:57:38,924
Edward heard the noise,
came downstairs,

959
00:57:39,536 --> 00:57:41,902
and then, of course,
Edward had to be killed, too

960
00:57:42,739 --> 00:57:43,728
Yes

961
00:57:46,676 --> 00:57:50,305
That must have been very close
to the way it happened

962
00:57:51,348 --> 00:57:52,372
Cake?

963
00:57:53,016 --> 00:57:55,712
No, thank you
Well, maybe Thanks

964
00:57:56,386 --> 00:57:57,819
Hey, they look delicious

965
00:58:00,423 --> 00:58:03,722
Lieutenant,
I better tell you something
before you find out yourself

966
00:58:04,394 --> 00:58:06,919
There's an artifact
missing from the museum

967
00:58:07,164 --> 00:58:08,654
What kind
of an artifact?

968
00:58:08,732 --> 00:58:09,664
It's gold

969
00:58:09,733 --> 00:58:12,566
It's a small,
rectangular piece
with carved stripes on it

970
00:58:13,303 --> 00:58:15,294
It's worth
quite a lot of money

971
00:58:15,505 --> 00:58:17,564
It's been missing
about two weeks

972
00:58:17,841 --> 00:58:20,139
Did you report it
to the insurance company?

973
00:58:20,911 --> 00:58:22,811
No, no Edward
didn't want me to

974
00:58:23,313 --> 00:58:24,712
Why not, ma'am?

975
00:58:24,781 --> 00:58:26,681
Well, he said
he knew who had taken it

976
00:58:26,750 --> 00:58:29,014
and he preferred to take care
of the matter himself

977
00:58:29,386 --> 00:58:30,444
Did he tell you who?

978
00:58:30,520 --> 00:58:32,215
No Edward was
a very stern man

979
00:58:32,289 --> 00:58:35,656
He wasn't given to
emotional outbursts
any more than I am

980
00:58:36,159 --> 00:58:37,421
Except this one time,

981
00:58:37,928 --> 00:58:39,828
two weeks ago,
about the artifact

982
00:58:40,664 --> 00:58:43,497
I told him that I was going
to report it no matter what,

983
00:58:43,967 --> 00:58:45,798
and I thought
he was going to strike me

984
00:58:45,869 --> 00:58:47,530
He went into a rage

985
00:58:47,604 --> 00:58:48,730
Who else had access?

986
00:58:49,573 --> 00:58:50,562
I did

987
00:58:51,908 --> 00:58:54,433
Yes, but who else,
Miss Lytton?

988
00:58:55,345 --> 00:58:56,369
No one

989
00:58:56,713 --> 00:58:57,702
No one at all?

990
00:58:58,748 --> 00:59:00,045
Not to my knowledge

991
00:59:00,717 --> 00:59:04,175
Miss Lytton, Janie's friend,
the man that she was with
at 9:00,

992
00:59:05,355 --> 00:59:07,789
that was Mr Shaeffer's
brother, wasn't it?

