Lieutenant, I don't know
what you're talking about

1232
01:12:49,111 --> 01:12:53,070
And you never will,
Mrs Brandt, unless
this case goes to trial

1233
01:12:54,417 --> 01:12:56,510
And then
it will all come out

1234
01:12:58,120 --> 01:13:01,612
What your brother said to you
about something being missing

1235
01:13:03,793 --> 01:13:05,488
And what you said to me

1236
01:13:06,462 --> 01:13:07,451
Janie,

1237
01:13:13,636 --> 01:13:16,764
it wasn't true
what he told you about
my killing your father

1238
01:13:20,443 --> 01:13:21,933
Was it, Lieutenant?

1239
01:13:24,380 --> 01:13:26,678
You lied about that,
didn't you?

1240
01:13:29,385 --> 01:13:31,148
Tell her
it wasn't true

1241
01:13:32,722 --> 01:13:34,713
Tell her

1242
01:13:35,191 --> 01:13:36,886
It was all such
a long time ago

1243
01:13:36,959 --> 01:13:39,223
It couldn't matter
to anyone anymore

1244
01:13:41,130 --> 01:13:42,222
Only to Janie

1245
01:13:44,900 --> 01:13:46,060
Yes, ma'am

1246
01:13:47,470 --> 01:13:48,459
It wasn't true

1247
01:13:50,072 --> 01:13:51,699
I lied about that

1248
01:13:56,445 --> 01:13:59,710
It won't be necessary to use
the tapes as evidence,
Lieutenant

1249
01:14:02,685 --> 01:14:04,084
Yes, ma'am

1250
01:14:26,175 --> 01:14:27,267
Lieutenant,

1251
01:14:30,346 --> 01:14:31,745
may I take your arm?

1252
01:14:36,919 --> 01:14:38,318
It's my pleasure,
Miss Lytton

